OL,3,CFamily weeps as boy found guilty of
OL,4,Cmurdering teenager Alfie Lewis
OL,6,FHe then ran home and was arrested a
OL,7,Fshort time later. He had admitted
OL,8,Fpossessing a knife but denied murder.
OL,10,FHe claimed he was scared of Alfie
OL,11,Ffollowing a number of previous
OL,12,Fincidents and had acted in self-
OL,13,Fdefence, but the jury convicted him of
OL,14,Fmurder after around nine hours of
OL,15,Fdeliberations.
OL,17,FThe trial has been conducted by
OL,18,Fbarristers not wearing formal robes
OL,19,Fand wigs because of the age of the
OL,20,Fdefendant.
